-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -1.838ex; width:11.789ex; height:3.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
lim _{n\to \infty }a_{n}=3DL}"></span>
is read as:
</p>
<div class=3D"block-indent">The limit of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a<sub>n=
</sub></i></span> as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:itali=
c;">n</span> approaches infinity equals <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">L</span></div><p> or <link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-i=
nline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r996643573"></p><div class=3D"b=
lock-indent">The limit as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">n</span> approaches infinity of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a<sub>n=
</sub></i></span> equals <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:i=
talic;">L</span>.</div>
<p>The formal definition intuitively means that eventually, all elements of=
 the sequence get arbitrarily close to the limit, since the <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Absolute_value" title=3D"Absolute value">absolute=
 value</a> <span class=3D"texhtml">|<span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding=
-left:0.1em; padding-right:0.1em;"><i>a</i><sub><i>n</i></sub> =E2=88=92 <i=
>L</i></span>|</span> is the distance between <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a<=
/i><sub><i>n</i></sub></span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fon=
t-style:italic;">L</span>.=20
</p><p>Not every sequence has a limit. A sequence with a limit is called <i=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convergent_series" title=3D"Conve=
rgent series">convergent</a></i>; otherwise it is called <i>divergent</i>. =
One can show that a convergent sequence has only one limit.
</p><p>The limit of a sequence and the limit of a function are closely rela=
ted. On one hand, the limit as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-s=
tyle:italic;">n</span> approaches infinity of a sequence <span class=3D"tex=
html">{<i>a</i><sub><i>n</i></sub>}</span> is simply the limit at infinity =
of a function <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i>(<i>n</i>)</span>=E2=80=94def=
ined on the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_number" title=
=3D"Natural number">natural numbers</a> <span class=3D"texhtml">{<i>n</i>}<=
/span>. On the other hand, if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-st=
yle:italic;">X</span> is the domain of a function <span class=3D"texhtml"><=
i>f</i>(<i>x</i>)</span> and if the limit as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" s=
tyle=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> approaches infinity of <span class=3D"=
texhtml"><i>f</i>(<i>x</i><sub><i>n</i></sub>)</span> is <span class=3D"tex=
html mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">L</span> for <i>every</i> arbitrary=
 sequence of points <span class=3D"texhtml">{<i>x</i><sub><i>n</i></sub>}</=
span> in <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>X</i> =E2=88=92 <i>x</i><sub>0</sub></s=
pan> which converges to <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i><sub>0</sub></span>=
, then the limit of the function <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>f</i>(<i>x</i>)=
</span> as <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i></span> approaches <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i><sub>0</sub></span> is equal to <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">L</span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limit_(mathematics)=
#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup> One such sequence would be <span class=3D"texhtm=
l">{<i>x</i><sub>0</sub> + 1/<i>n</i>}</span>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Infinity_as_a_limit">Infini=
ty as a limit</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DLimit_(mathematics)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit sec=
tion: Infinity as a limit"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsecti=
on-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>There is also a notion of having a limit "tend to infinity", rather than=
 to a finite value <span class=3D"nowrap"><span class=3D"mwe-math-element m=
we-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-math=
