<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Infinity_in_limits_of_funct=
ions">Infinity in limits of functions</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/w/index.php?title=3DLimit_(mathematics)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=
=3D13" title=3D"Edit section: Infinity in limits of functions"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>It is possible to define the notion of "tending to infinity" in the doma=
in of <span class=3D"nowrap"><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-eleme=
nt-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" styl=
e=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alt=
text=3D"{\displaystyle f}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>f</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle f}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/132e57acb643253e7810ee9702d9581f159a1c61" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:1.279ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle f}"=
></span>,</span>
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \lim _{x\rightarrow +\infty }f(x)=3DL.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <munder>
          <mo movablelimits=3D"true" form=3D"prefix">lim</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">=E2=86=92<!-- =E2=86=92 --></mo>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=E2=88=9E<!-- =E2=88=9E --></mi>
          </mrow>
        </munder>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>L</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lim _{x\righ=
tarrow +\infty }f(x)=3DL.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/e2e6069260dbaec28ad9996125b02a049a8ba33a" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.005ex; width:15.638ex; height:4.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
lim _{x\rightarrow +\infty }f(x)=3DL.}"></span>
</p><p>This could be considered equivalent to the limit as a reciprocal ten=
ds to 0:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \lim _{x'\rightarrow 0^{+}}f(1/x')=3DL.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <munder>
          <mo movablelimits=3D"true" form=3D"prefix">lim</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msup>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo>=E2=80=B2</mo>
            </msup>
            <mo stretchy=3D"false">=E2=86=92<!-- =E2=86=92 --></mo>
            <msup>
              <mn>0</mn>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mo>+</mo>
              </mrow>
            </msup>
          </mrow>
        </munder>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo>/</mo>
        </mrow>
        <msup>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo>=E2=80=B2</mo>
        </msup>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>L</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \lim _{x'\rig=
htarrow 0^{+}}f(1/x')=3DL.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d787091daec9ebd309895712e87bf3a585e6c070" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.338ex; width:18.282ex; height:4.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
lim _{x'\rightarrow 0^{+}}f(1/x')=3DL.}"></span>
</p><p>or it can be defined directly: the "limit of <span class=3D"mwe-math=
